{"id":25666,"date":"2017-12-21T12:13:59","date_gmt":"2017-12-21T08:13:59","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=25666"},"modified":"2019-05-21T15:36:02","modified_gmt":"2019-05-21T11:36:02","slug":"prophet-more-mercy-ourselves","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/12\/21\/prophet-more-mercy-ourselves\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Rahmah: The Prophet more merciful to us than ourselves"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Umaymah bint Ruqayqah reported: I pledged allegiance to the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, with a group of women. The Prophet said to us, \u201c<strong>In so far as you are able and capable<\/strong>.\u201d I said, \u201cAllah and his messenger are more merciful to us than we are to ourselves.\u201d And I said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, accept our pledge,\u201d meaning shake our hands. The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>Verily, my statement to one hundred women is like my statement to one woman.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>In another narration, the Prophet said, \u201c<strong>Verily, I do not shake hands with women<\/strong>.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 1597<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih<\/em><\/strong> (authentic) according to Al-Albani<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u0646 \u0623\u0645\u064a\u0645\u0629 \u0628\u0646\u062a \u0631\u0642\u064a\u0642\u0629 \u0642\u0627\u0644\u062a \u0628\u064e\u0627\u064a\u064e\u0639\u0652\u062a\u064f \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0641\u0650\u064a \u0646\u0650\u0633\u0652\u0648\u064e\u0629\u064d \u0641\u064e\u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0644\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0627 <strong>\u0641\u0650\u064a\u0645\u064e\u0627 \u0627\u0633\u0652\u062a\u06